<item>
            <title>[SPARK-29160] Event log file is written without specific charset which should be ideally UTF-8</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29160</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue is from observation by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vanzin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vanzin&quot;&gt;vanzin&lt;/a&gt;&#160;: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/25670#discussion_r325383512&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/25670#discussion_r325383512&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Quoting his comment here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a long standing bug in the original code, but this should be explicitly setting the charset to UTF-8 (using&#160;new PrintWriter(new OutputStreamWriter(...)).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reader side should too, although doing that now could potentially break old logs... we should open a bug for this.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While EventLoggingListener writes to UTF-8 properly when converting to byte[] before writing, it doesn&apos;t deal with charset in logEvent().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be fixed, but as Marcelo said, we also need to be aware of potential broken of reading old logs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
